Global Air Transport USM Market Insights
Air Transport USM Market size was valued at USD 120 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 180 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6% from 2024 to 2030.

Air Transport USM Market Overview
The Air Transport USM (Used Serviceable Material) market is expected to reach a market value of approximately USD 8.5 billion by 2028, growing at a significant CAGR over the forecast period. The increasing demand for air travel and the need for cost-efficient solutions in the aviation industry drive the adoption of used parts and materials for maintenance, repair, and overhaul (MRO) services. Airlines and MRO service providers are increasingly relying on USM as a sustainable and cost-effective alternative to new spare parts, especially given the economic pressure and fluctuating fuel prices in the industry.

